<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none'><span

;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:4.5in;text-align:justify;text-ind=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:4.5in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
.5in;mso-hyphenate:none'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-fami=
ly:
Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>August 2007<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:4.5in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
.5in;mso-hyphenate:none'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-fami=
ly:
Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><b style=3D=
'mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-s=
pacing:
-.15pt'>2007-2008 Part 154 Comprehensive Plan and Reporting Requirements <o=
:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><b style=3D=
'mso-bidi-font-weight:
normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-s=
pacing:
-.15pt'>for the Education of Limited English Proficient (LEP) Students <o:p=
></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-1.0in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-s=
pacing:
-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Chapter
57 of the Laws of 2007 requires that, beginning with the 2007-08 school yea=
r,
each school district receiving Total Foundation Aid<i style=3D'mso-bidi-fon=
t-style:
normal'> </i>must develop a comprehensive plan to meet the educational need=
s of
students with limited English proficiency (&#8220;LEP&#8221;), consistent w=
ith
Commissioner&#8217;s regulations (&#8220;CR&#8221;).<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Part 154 of the
Commissioner&#8217;s regulations governs services for pupils with limited
English proficiency.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Prior to=
 the
enactment of Chapter 57 of the Laws of 2007, school districts had the optio=
n of
claiming separate State aid for the education of LEP pupils.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Compliance with various requiremen=
ts of
Part 154 depended on whether the district claimed such aid.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Separate LEP aid is no longer avai=
lable
to school districts beginning in school year 2007-08.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>Instead, all districts will receive
Total Foundation Aid and must comply with Part 154 of the Commissioner&#821=
7;s regulations.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span><span style=3D'letter-spacing:-.15=
pt'><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>In
June 2007, CR Part 154 was amended, effective July 1, 2007. <a
href=3D"http://www.regents.nysed.gov/2007Meetings/June2007/0607emscvesida1.=
htm">http://www.regents.nysed.gov/2007Meetings/June2007/0607emscvesida1.htm=
</a>
CR 154.3 requires all school districts receiving Total Foundation Aid,
including community school districts, to develop a Comprehensive Plan to me=
et
the educational needs of LEP students.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>CR 154.3 (a) requires=
 that
the Plan must include:<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.75in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-.25in;mso-list:l11 level1 lfo6;mso-list-change:\F0B7 " " 20070809T1442;
tab-stops:list 13.5pt .5in'><![if !supportLists]><span style=3D'mso-bidi-fo=
nt-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Symbol;mso-fareast-font-family:Symbol;mso-bidi-font-fami=
ly:
Symbol'><span style=3D'mso-list:Ignore'>&middot;<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "=
Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;

  style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:1=

  </td>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:8.1pt;mso-hyphenate:none'><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.=
0pt;
font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'margin-bottom:8.1pt;text-align=
:center;
mso-hyphenate:none'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Program
Guidelines<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>The following pages provide
general guidelines regarding programs for LEP students as well as instructi=
ons and
forms to be completed for the development of the Comprehensive Plan and for=
 the
completion and submission of the required reports.</span><u><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p></o:p></span></u=
></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'margin-bottom:8.1pt;text-align=
:center;
mso-hyphenate:none'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-bottom:8.1pt;mso-hyphenate:none'><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.=
0pt;
font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>Commissioner&#8217;s Regulations f=
or
LEP Students</span></b><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family=
:Arial;
letter-spacing:-.15pt'><span style=3D'mso-tab-count:1'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=
bsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Parts
117 and 154 of the Regulations of the Commissioner of Education relate to t=
he
screening of new entrants and services for LEP students.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span>CR Part 154 prescribes the specific
requirements for the implementation of instructional programs and activities
for LEP students.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p>=
</span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>CR Part
154 was instituted to ensure that LEP students receive appropriate services=
 in
order to acquire and develop English language skills and meet the standards=
 in
the core subjects expected at their grade and age levels.<span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Research on effective progra=
ms for
LEP students identifies Seven Essential Elements. The Board of Regents has
incorporated these elements into their Twelve Action Steps to assist LEP
students in meeting the English language arts standards. (Please refer to
Appendices A and B attached for a copy of each of these two documents.)<o:p=
></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight=
:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Eligible
Students<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight=
:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Students
eligible to receive services under CR Part 154 are those identified as stud=
ents
with limited English proficiency (LEP).<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nb=
sp;
</span>LEP students are those who come from a home where a language other t=
han
English is spoken and score below a State designated level of proficiency on
the Language Assessment Battery-Revised<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nb=
sp;
</span>(LAB-R) or the New York State English as a Second Language Achieveme=
nt
Test (NYSESLAT), as set forth in CR Part 154. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:1.75in;text-align:justify;text-in=
dent:
-1.75in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weigh=
t:
normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-s=
pacing:
-.15pt'>Types of Programs-- Bilingual and English as a Second Language</spa=
n></b><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
> <b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'>(ESL) Instructional Programs<o:p></o:=
p></b></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight=
:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.5in;text-align:justify;text-inde=
nt:-.5in;
mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in 0in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:1=
2.0pt;
font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><span style=3D'mso-tab-count:1'>&n=
bsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><u>=
Bilingual
education programs</u><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'> </b>must be
implemented in school districts with an enrollment of 20 or more LEP studen=
ts
with the same native language other than English at the same grade level in=
 the
same building. The bilingual education program includes two components: a
language arts instructional component and a content area instructional
component. The language arts instructional component is delivered through
instruction in English language arts, English as a second language and nati=
ve
language arts. The content area instructional component is delivered though
instruction in the native language and English through ESL methodologies.<o=
:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-siz=
e:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-siz=
e:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-siz=
e:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><u><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
>Freestanding
ESL programs </span></u><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-famil=
y:
Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>must be implemented in school districts which =
have
fewer than 20 LEP students at the same grade level in the same building who
speak the same native language other than English. The freestanding ESL pro=
gram
includes two components: a language arts instructional component and a cont=
ent
area instructional component. The language arts instructional component is
delivered through instruction in English language arts and English as a sec=
ond
language. The content area instructional component is delivered through
instruction in English and ESL methodologies.<u><o:p></o:p></u></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'=
><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-2.0in;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-stops:-.5in'><b><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-=
size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt;mso-bidi-font-style:italic'>=
Required
Units of Study</span></b><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-fami=
ly:
Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:i=
talic'><o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>Public school districts are required to provide t=
he
amount of English language instruction specified in CR 154.2 (d) and (e). As
specified in Action Step 1, the English language arts standards are the bas=
is
for the Native Language Arts, English as a Second Language and English Lang=
uage
Arts curricula. The chart that follows identifies the required units of stu=
dy
for each of these disciplines. Please note that a unit of study is equivale=
nt
to 180 minutes per week.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'font-size:=
11.5pt;
mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

  <p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><b

  <p class=3DMsoNormal align=3Dcenter style=3D'text-align:center'><b
  style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;mso=

  10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>GRADES K-8<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>
  </td>
  <td width=3D288 colspan=3D3 valign=3Dtop style=3D'width:3.0in;border-top:=
none;

Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><span style=3D'mso-tab-count:1'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=
bsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></i></b>=
<span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt;
mso-bidi-font-weight:bold;mso-bidi-font-style:italic'>T</span><span
style=3D'font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>he Language Assessment
Battery-Revised (LAB-R) is the only approved test for the identification of=
 students
as limited English proficient. Similarly, the New York State English as a
Second Language Achievement Test (NYSESLAT) is the only approved test for
measuring LEP students&#8217; level of English proficiency annually, to
determine whether or not the student continues to be LEP. <o:p></o:p></span=
></p>

</o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:2.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none'><span
style=3D'font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>The New York State Educat=
ion
Department's Office of Bilingual Education and Foreign Language Studies
(OBE-FLS) provides on-going technical assistance to school districts on iss=
ues
related to the education of LEP students and in the preparation of the requ=
ired
2007-2008 Comprehensive Plan and reports.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&=
nbsp;
</span>If assistance is needed, contact the office at (518) 474-8775 or acc=
ess
the web page at <a href=3D"http://www.emsc.nysed.gov/ciai/nysben.html">http=
://www.emsc.nysed.gov/ciai/nysben.html</a><o:p></o:p></span></p>

style=3D'font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span><=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-hyphenate:none;tab-sto=
ps:-.5in'><span
style=3D'font-family:Arial;letter-spacing:-.15pt'>The Department's document
entitled &quot;Guidelines for Programs under Part 154 of Commissioner's
Regulations for Pupils with Limited English Proficiency,&quot; currently in
draft form, (referred to as Part 154 Guidelines) provides information on
appropriate practices and procedures for the education of LEP students. The
following Department documents are also valuable resources for the
implementation of programs for LEP students: &#8220;The Teaching of Language
Arts to Limited English Proficient/English Language Learners: A Resource Gu=
ide
for All Teachers&#8221; and &#8220;The Teaching of Language Arts to Limited
English Proficient/English language Learners: Learning Standards for Englis=
h as
a Second Language.&#8221;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

Assistance Centers (<span class=3DSpellE>BETAC's</span>) are also available=

t the
BETAC in their region. Information on your regional <span class=3DSpellE>BE=

is available at the OBE-FLS web page: <a

font-family:Arial'>students enrolled in nonpublic schools. <o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span

an></p>

  style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o=
:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
  <p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
  style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'>LE=
P students
  who have not met the performance standard in writing<o:p></o:p></span></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
 <tr style=3D'mso-yfti-irow:8;mso-yfti-lastrow:yes'>
  <td width=3D150 valign=3Dtop style=3D'width:112.45pt;border-top:none;bord=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'font-size:11.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p=
>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>The school providing
services to the students in 2006-07 must make requests for extension of ser=
vices
for the 2007-2008 school year. The report must include the names of all such
students, including those that were in the school in 2006-07 and moved to
another NYS public school in 2007-2008 (i.e., transfer students, 6<sup>th</=
sup>,
8th or 9th grade graduates.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>School districts may =
make
requests for other reasons.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
</span>However, vague reasons such as consultant teachers, dual language, o=
pted
out, behavior problems, heterogeneous group in English, etc<i style=3D'mso-=
bidi-font-style:
normal'>.</i> will not be approved<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>An extension of servi=
ces
will not be granted for students for whom no assessment or an assessment ot=
her
than the NYSESLAT is provided.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;tab-stops:-1.0in -.5in 0in =
.2in .4in .5in .6in .8in 1.0in 1.2in 1.4in 1.5in 1.6in 1.8in 2.0in 2.2in 2.=
4in 2.5in 2.6in 3.0in 3.5in 4.0in 4.5in 5.0in 5.5in 6.0in 6.5in 7.0in 7.5in=
'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>A description of the
interventions that are being implemented, above and beyond Academic Interve=
ntion
Services (AIS), to help students for whom a request for extension of servic=
es
is submitted must be provided. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;</span><o:=
p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>All schools in <st1:p=
lace
w:st=3D"on"><st1:City w:st=3D"on">New York City</st1:City></st1:place> must=
 comply
with the Consent Decree and the Lau Compliance Plan. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;mso-outl=
ine-level:
1;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-style:it=
alic'>Parental
Transfer/Withdrawal Option<o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;mso-outl=
ine-level:
1;tab-stops:-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=
an></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:.25in;text-align:justify;mso-outl=
ine-level:
1;tab-stops:-1.25in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:A=
rial;
mso-bidi-font-weight:bold'>Parents of a newly enrolled LEP student must be
informed of their child&#8217;s placement in a bilingual or ESL instruction=
al
program. In addition to informing parents of their child&#8217;s placement =
in
any of these programs, districts must advise parents of the transfer/withdr=
awal
option afforded to them under CR Part 154. This transfer/withdrawal option =
is
specified below.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyTextIndent2 style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justif=
y'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"=
Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyTextIndent2 style=3D'margin-left:22.5pt;text-align:justif=
y'><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.=
0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Withdrawal from a
bilingual education program:</span></b><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12=
.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> The parents or o=
ther
persons in parental relation to a pupil designated as limited English profi=
cient
shall have the option to withdraw their child from participation in an
instructional bilingual education program, provided that:<o:p></o:p></span>=
</p>

<p class=3DMsoBodyTextIndent2 style=3D'margin-left:22.5pt;text-align:justif=
y'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"=
Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-.5in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo18;mso-list-change:"\(%1\:1\:2\:\)" " " 2007081=
3T1433;
tab-stops:list 1.0in'><![if !supportLists]><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-siz=
e:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-fareast-font-family:Arial'><span style=3D'mso-=
list:
Ignore'>(i)<span style=3D'font:7.0pt "Times New Roman"'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=
nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs=
p;
</span></span></span><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>the parents or ot=
her
persons in parental relation to a pupil designated as limited English
proficient meet with the school principal along with the school or district
supervisor of bilingual education to discuss and explain further the nature,
purposes, educational values of the program and the skills required of
personnel;<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-f=
ont-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp=
;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:1.0in;text-align:justify;text-ind=
ent:
-.5in'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-=
font-family:
"Times New Roman"'>(ii)<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp; </span><span
style=3D'mso-tab-count:1'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>as a minimu=
m such
pupil shall participate in a English as a second language instructional
program.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"=
Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.=
0pt;
font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'>Transfer from an =
ESL
into a bilingual education program:</span></b><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-=
size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman"'> In a scho=
ol
building where the number of eligible pupils does not require the offering =
of a
bilingual education program, parents or other persons in parental relation =
to a
pupil identified as limited English proficient shall have the option of
transferring their child to a school within the district provided such prog=
ram
is available at such other school.<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;
</span>A parent who chooses not to exercise the transfer option shall be
informed that his or her child shall participate in a English as a second
language instructional program. Parents of appropriately identified LEP
students do not have the option to withdraw their children from an ESL
instructional program. Signed parent letters exercising the withdrawal/tran=
sfer
option must be kept in the student&#8217;s cumulative record.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"=
Times New Roman"'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial;mso-bidi-font-family:"=
Times New Roman"'>School
districts required to submit copies of the Comprehensive Plan (see page 2) =
and
that have bilingual instructional programs must attach sample copies of the
transfer/withdrawal option letters sent to parents.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify;mso-outline-level:1;tab-st=
ops:
-.5in'><b style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><u><span style=3D'mso-bidi-=
font-size:
12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p><span style=3D'text-decoration:none'>&nbsp;<=
/span></o:p></span></u></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><b
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-weight:normal'><span style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.=
0pt;
font-family:Arial'>LEP Student Evaluation<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&=
nbsp;
</span><o:p></o:p></span></b></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></sp=

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span
style=3D'mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Arial'>State assessment data=
 for
LEP students must be coordinated and submitted through the New York State
Education Department&#8217;s data collection system. <o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'margin-left:27.0pt;text-align:justify'><span

<p class=3DMsoNormal style=3D'text-align:justify'><span style=3D'font-size:=
10.5pt;
font-family:Arial'>I hereby certify and assure the State Education Departme=
nt
that the Statement of Assurances were approved by the Board of Education of
this LEA and are consistent with the requirements set forth in Section 3204=
 of
the Education Law, relating to the education of LEP students and with the
requirements of Part 117 and 154 of the Regulations of the Commissioner of
Education concerning the education of pupils with limited English proficien=
cy.
I further assure the State Education Department that this LEA is in complia=
nce
with such said laws and regulations.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBlockText style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:.9pt;margin-bo=
ttom:
0in;margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;tab-stops:ce=
nter 5.0in left 751.5pt'><span
style=3D'font-size:10.0pt'>*<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=
bsp;
</span>The number of teachers reported must represent the number of teachers
holding an appropriate license for the subject area being taught (i.e.,
language arts and content area.)<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBlockText style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:.9pt;margin-bo=
ttom:
0in;margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;tab-stops:ce=
nter 5.0in left 751.5pt'><span
style=3D'font-size:10.0pt'><span
style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Note: The =
Office
of Bilingual Education and Foreign Language Studies will conduct a random
review of the 2006-2007 teacher reported data. Districts randomly selected =
will
be asked to electronically submit to the Department, the name of the
teacher(s), social security number and type of license or certificate issue=
d by
the NYSED.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBlockText style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:.9pt;margin-bo=
ttom:
0in;margin-left:.75in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;tab-stops:ce=
nter 5.0in left 751.5pt'><span
style=3D'font-size:10.0pt'>**<span style=3D'mso-spacerun:yes'>&nbsp;&nbsp;
</span>Examples of this may include: teachers without an appropriate <st1:P=
laceName
w:st=3D"on">New York</st1:PlaceName> <st1:PlaceType w:st=3D"on">State</st1:=
PlaceType>
teaching certificate or <st1:place w:st=3D"on"><st1:City w:st=3D"on">New Yo=
rk City</st1:City></st1:place>
license for the subject area(s) being taught or without a valid NYS teachin=
g certificate
or NYC license.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoBlockText style=3D'margin-top:0in;margin-right:.9pt;margin-bo=
ttom:
0in;margin-left:45.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-9.0pt;tab-stops:9=
.0pt center 5.0in left 751.5pt'><span
style=3D'font-size:10.0pt'>*** Teaching Assistants and Paraprofessionals mu=
st be
working under the direct supervision of a licensed teacher.<span
style=3D'mso-tab-count:1'>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><o:p></o:p></span=

     as a second language (ESL) and English language arts (ELA) curricula
